Inheritence is the mechanism of aquiring one class's property by another class 
the class from which the property is derived is called parent class or super class or base class
the class which aquires the property is called child class or sub class or derived class

NOTE: Private members of the parent class are not inherited by the child class. Only public and protected members are inherited.

Types of inheritence:
    --> Single-Level inheritence: Where there is only one parent class and one child class
    --> Multiple inheritence: when a child class inherits from more than one parent class
    --> Multilevel inheritence: when a child class inherits from a parent class which is also a child class of another parent class
    --> Hierarchical inheritence: when multiple child classes inherit from a single parent class
    --> Hybrid inheritence: when a combination of two or more types of inheritence is used